Sentencas: A geometrical model was developed to predict the influences of solid grain size, pore size and porosity on the triple-phase-boundary (TPB) length in electronic composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Geometrical modeling of the triple-phase-boundary in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It shows that the TPB length is inversely proportional to grain size and can be optimized by the pore size and porosity.
Titulo: Geometrical modeling of the triple-phase-boundary in solid oxide fuel cells
